                        </p>
                        <p>
                           Why Choose the "Build a Bridge" Activity? 
                        </p>
                        <p>
                           ● Bridges are a perfect example of triangular prisms in engineering. Many bridges use triangular trusses because they:</p>
                           <p>  Distribute weight evenly</p>
                           <p> Provide structural stability</p>
                            <p>Are used in real-life construction
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            ● By building a model bridge, students get to see, touch and manipulate triangular prisms, helping them connect abstract mathematical concepts to real-world engineering.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                             <m>\textbf{More Than Just Math!} </m></p>

                            <p>The <m>\textbf{"Build a Bridge"} </m>activity isn't just about calculating volume—it’s about seeing math in action! 
                        </p>
